<title>UK: HTV lifts half year pretax profit 10 percent.</title>
<headline>HTV lifts half year pretax profit 10 percent.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-10-02</dateline>
<text>
<p>Six months to June 30</p>
<p>			   (million stg unless stated)</p>
<p> Shr (pence)		5.7		    vs 5.0</p>
<p> Dividend (pence)	 1.4		    vs 1.25</p>
<p> Pretax		     6.7		    vs 6.1</p>
<p>NOTE - Analysts' forecasts on pre-tax profits at HTV Group Plc, the Welsh and West of England independent television franchise operator, were in a range of 6.4 to 6.7 million stg.  </p>
<p> Turnover		   69.1		   vs 66.4</p>
<p> Operating result	 6.9		    vs 6.3</p>
<p> Interest		   0.2		    vs 0.2</p>
<p> Tax			  1.7		    vs 1.7 charge</p>
<p> Attributable	     5.0		    vs 4.4</p>
<p> Pay date		   Nov 15</p>
<p>Div registration date  Oct 22  Ex-div date		Oct 14</p>
<p>NOTE -- HTV Group said long-term prospects were &quot;very good&quot; although in the short term, full year advertising revenue would see only modest year-on-year growth. The group noted that it saw a strong independent future for the company.</p>
<p>-- London Newsroom +44 1271 542 4017</p>
</text>
